<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Wet1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Wet,</orth> adj. consisting of water, or moistened with water (or tears); and generally opposed to dry: <bibl n="shak. ven 83" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 83</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 83" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 83</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.7.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 7, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 35</bibl>. Substantively: <cit><quote>applying w. to w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 40" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 40</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>messenger of w.</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.157" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 157</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>